post_text:
Hello! I am excited to introduce myself – My name is Paula Anderson, and I am the new Ogilvie Musical Director. I have been active in the Ogilvie theater department in the past, and I am delighted that I get the chance to return. About four years ago I went back to college to receive my Associate of Fine Arts in Theater. I have been working in educational and professional theaters in the Twin Cities metro area for the past three years, but I am very excited to be back in my home school district sharing my passion for theater and love of education.

Good News! We have acquired the rights for the show and chosen the performance dates. Mark March 12th-15th! We will be announcing the show title soon, watch your Facebook news feed for this announcement coming soon.

post_text:
I would like to take a moment to say thank you. Thank you to the parents who have supported this program, thank you to the staff who have supported this program and thank you to the students who believe enough in the power the theatre to have joined me on stage and back stage these past six years.

My journey at Ogilvie has now come to an end. I know that this decision will be met with sadness and even anger. This decision was NOT an easy one. There have been countless sleepless nights and weighing both the pros and cons of moving on. Ultimately, I needed to do what was best for myself and my family.

There is a saying in show business that the "show must go on" and that is what I would expect from this department, the students in this department and the adults who support this program. Theatre is important and has great value within our lives.

Wishing you the best,
Mr. Walker

The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society, MN, ND, SD
April 23, 2018 at 8:30 AM ·

VOTING IS NOW CLOSED!

It’s time for our Annual Pennies for Patients Fun & Funky Awards! This week, we’re recognizing some of the best photos and ideas to come from our Pennies for Patients partners this school year.

Here’s how it works… WE nominate schools in four different categories, YOU vote on your favorite photo and help that school earn a $20 Target gift card!

Today we’re excited to kick things off by sharing the nominees for Best Coin Photo! Each photo has been numbered 1-4, place a vote by commenting below with the number of your favorite pic featuring students with coins! Voting is open until Thursday at midnight, on Friday we crown the winner!

post_text: The castlist is officially posted. You may get scripts and officially accept you part with Mr. Walker starting tomorrow. Your first rehearsal will be Monday, December 11th from 8:00 to 2:00 pm. Congratulations to the entire cast!

post_text: Wow! Congratulations to the students who auditioned for Willy Wonka. You showed up in record numbers the last three days and are in the process of creating an absolutely AMAZING cast and a marvelous show. The work is just beginning, but your directors are ready to match your intensity and work as hard as you do. 😁

post_text: Auditions for Willy Wonka and the Chocolate Factory will be held on the stage today and tomorrow from 3:45 until 6:00. You MUST have signed up for your audition time prior to your arrival. Please plan on being 10 minutes early to fill out you audition form. If you cannot make these times please see Mr. Walker.
